Suspected Taraba State kidnap kingpin, Bala Hamisu, popularly known as Wadume, and Jolly Nyame, a former governor of the state convicted for fraud are “best of friends” at the Kuje Correctional Centre, Abuja, a top official has told SaharaReporters. Nyame, who governed Taraba from 1999 to 2007, was in 2018 sentenced to 14 years in prison by Justice Adebukola Banjoko of the Federal Capital Territory High Court, Abuja for stealing N1.6billionn from the state’s treasury.  The former governor then appealed the judgment of the trial court and the jail term was reduced to 12 years, the Appeal Court judgment was also upheld by the Supreme Court. In April, the Council of States after a meeting in Abuja agreed to free Nyame, former Governor Joshua Dariye (Plateau) and 157 other convicts. However, few weeks after the pardon was granted, the former Taraba governor is yet to be released by the prison authorities. A top prison official during the weekend said Wadume, who is awaiting trial, is the closest person to Nyame in the facility.



