7 Months Ago The duo were said to be kept in a block called “VIP” and are allowed to enjoy certain privileges not permitted by the prison rules and regulations. “While Nyame is in VIP custody 3 down, Wadume is in VIP custody 4 down. Both are living large like kings. Wadume though staying in a VIP room has two other people staying with him while Nyame stays alone in a room,” the prison official said. “However, Wadume is always with Governor Nyame from morning to late evening before going back to his room. They are very close and best of friends.” The official added that Wadume had been bragging to other inmates, claiming some powerful Nigerian politicians are working behind the scene to truncate his case. “Judgment on his case will be delivered on June 10 but he has been bragging all about that he would be discharged and acquitted; that he has powerful politicians behind him,” the source added.



